abstract: I have long seen wheelchairs as the enemy. That’s going to have to change.
snippet: I have long seen wheelchairs as the enemy. That’s going to have to change.
lead_paragraph: For several years now, I’ve had a difficult relationship with wheelchairs.

abstract: Across much of the Islamic world, many Muslims are disillusioned with the ugly things done in the name of their religion.
snippet: Across much of the Islamic world, many Muslims are disillusioned with the ugly things done in the name of their religion.
lead_paragraph: For decades, social scientists studying Islam discussed whether this second biggest religion of the world would go through the major transformation that the biggest one, Christianity, went through: secularization. Would Islam also lose its hegemony over public life, to become a mere one among various voices, not the dominant one, in Muslim societies?

headline_main: Luke Perry, a Heartthrob Who Led With His Heart

abstract: She was arrested dozens of times, and Klan members threw Molotov cocktails into her yard — but that didn’t stop her fight for civil rights.
